text: COVID Data Tracker’s wastewater surveillance tab provides information on #COVID19 spread in communities. Currently, virus levels in wastewater are relatively low nationwide. Learn more: https://t.co/F4bAyObDp1. https://t.co/2MtRaZgxCO

COVID-Net data show that #COVID19 hospitalizations rates for kids ages 5-11 yrs went down in recent weeks but are still higher compared to rates for this group in July 2021. At-home #COVID19 test use was lower among adults who were Black, ages 75 years or older, had lower incomes, and had a high school level education or less. Equitable access to testing is important to limit spread and inform when to seek treatment. More: https://t.co/HoPFNvWpA7.

A new @CDCMMWR study finds that the use of at-home COVID-19 tests among adults with #COVID19-like illness was three times higher when the Omicron variant was widely circulating than during Delta. Learn more: https://t.co/HoPFNvWpA7. https://t.co/vCvFSmaXKs

Vaccines are one of public health’s greatest success stories. They’ve been saving lives for over a century. 

Today, #COVID19 vaccines are saving lives and helping protect people from severe illness and hospitalization.

Learn more: https://t.co/yJFqxDZW8J.

Growing evidence continues to show that #COVID19 vaccination during pregnancy is safe and effective. If you are pregnant, talk to your doctor about the benefits of getting vaccinated against #COVID19. Learn more: https://t.co/pBVlI6STf8. https://t.co/JikB9nK6Ap

COVID-19 testing in school is still critical to find infections before they spread and prevent outbreaks. Learn more about why you should sign your child up: https://t.co/dGUBTmcTp4. https://t.co/79H4D02EBQ

Staying up to date with your #COVID19 vaccines:

1. Helps protect you from severe illness & death from all known variants 
2. Lowers your risk of infection 
3. Slows the spread of COVID-19 
4. Helps slow the emergence of new variants

Find a vaccine: https://t.co/xbvNiaVJKV. https://t.co/1knbNe6GYi

The anti-parasite drug ivermectin is not authorized or approved by FDA for treating or preventing #COVID19. Large doses can cause symptoms like nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, & seizures. 
Learn more: https://t.co/RL1JxDdnJ8. #PoisonPreventionWeek https://t.co/VHKw9nBiHh

New CDC study: Among adults hospitalized with #COVID19, those who got 2 or 3 doses of Pfizer-BioNTech or Moderna vaccine had 90–95% less risk of dying or needing a ventilator than adults not vaccinated. Learn more: https://t.co/F4bAyObDp1. https://t.co/MkGwWbN1TE

#COVID19 has impacted people all over the U.S., especially those ages 65 yrs and older. Among this population are those in the Retired and Senior Volunteers Program under AmeriCorps Seniors. Learn more about how they serve older people during the pandemic: https://t.co/ySwMm6UeGO https://t.co/wyVg5WAWg0
